	•	They do not emerge from protons/neutrons
	•	They are elemental members of the Standard Model

Electrons:
	•	are not built from quarks
	•	are not created by proton–neutron interactions
	•	pre-exist as part of the universe’s lepton family
	•	were around long before atoms formed

So literally, physically:

Electrons are not reactions of nucleons.

